<http://dx.doi.org/10.5091/plecevo.98847.figure16>
    dc:description "Figure 16. Abildgaardia triflora. A. Habit. B. Two leaf bases. C. Leaf apex. D. Spikelet. E. Rachilla. F, G. Glume, complete and upper abscised part. H. Young floret. I. Style and branches. J. Nutlet with filaments. All from Robinson 2038. Scale bars: A = 40 mm; B, C, H-J = 2 mm; D-G = 5 mm. Drawn by Jane Browning, reproduced with permission from the artist, originally published in Browning et al. (2020)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/898167" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

